## Functions

### areLoadsReorderable() {#ac01b3bf4dda9266ec05d70b2f55281fa}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static bool areLoadsReorderable (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/loadinst">LoadInst</a> &#42; Use, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/loadinst">LoadInst</a> &#42; MayClobber)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
This does one-way checks to see if <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/use">Use</a> could theoretically be hoisted above MayClobber.

This will not check the other way around.

This assumes that, for the purposes of <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryssa">MemorySSA</a>, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/use">Use</a> comes directly after MayClobber, with no potentially clobbering operations in between them. (Where potentially clobbering ops are memory barriers, aliased stores, etc.)

Definition at line <a href="#l00256">256</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/memoryssa-cpp">MemorySSA.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### checkClobberSanity() {#a930e3a524f031bdb14fe281e4eff4219}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static LLVM&#95;ATTRIBUTE&#95;UNUSED void checkClobberSanity (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryaccess">MemoryAccess</a> &#42; Start, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryaccess">MemoryAccess</a> &#42; ClobberAt, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memorylocation">MemoryLocation</a> &amp; StartLoc, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryssa">MemorySSA</a> &amp; MSSA, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> UpwardsMemoryQuery &amp; Query, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/batchaaresults">BatchAAResults</a> &amp; AA, bool AllowImpreciseClobber=false)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Verifies that <code>Start</code> is clobbered by <code>ClobberAt</code>, and that nothing inbetween <code>Start</code> and <code>ClobberAt</code> can clobbers <code>Start</code>.

This is meant to be as simple and self-contained as possible. Because it uses no cache, etc., it can be relatively expensive.


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="Start">The <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryaccess">MemoryAccess</a> that we want to walk from.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="ClobberAt">A clobber for Start.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="StartLoc">The <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memorylocation">MemoryLocation</a> for Start.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="MSSA">The <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryssa">MemorySSA</a> instance that Start and ClobberAt belong to.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="Query">The <a href="/docs/api/structs/anonymous-namespace-memoryssa-cpp-/upwardsmemoryquery">UpwardsMemoryQuery</a> we used for our search.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="<a href=&quot;/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/aa&quot;>AA</a>">The <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#ae457f1cf451ed893666c4a384e58f8e5">AliasAnalysis</a> we used for our search.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="AllowImpreciseClobber">Always false, unless we do relaxed verify.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

</MemberDefinition>

<Link id="l00250" /><CodeLine lineNumber="250"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// This does one-way checks to see if Use could theoretically be hoisted above</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00252" /><CodeLine lineNumber="252"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00753" /><CodeLine lineNumber="753"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00754" /><CodeLine lineNumber="754"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Phi optimization algorithm tl;dr:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00755" /><CodeLine lineNumber="755"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   - Find the earliest def/phi, A, we can optimize to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00756" /><CodeLine lineNumber="756"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   - Find if all paths from the starting memory access ultimately reach A</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00757" /><CodeLine lineNumber="757"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///     - If not, optimization isn&#39;t possible.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00758" /><CodeLine lineNumber="758"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///     - Otherwise, walk from A to another clobber or phi, A&#39;.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00759" /><CodeLine lineNumber="759"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///       - If A&#39; is a def, we&#39;re done.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00760" /><CodeLine lineNumber="760"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///       - If A&#39; is a phi, try to optimize it.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00761" /><CodeLine lineNumber="761"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00805" /><CodeLine lineNumber="805"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// FIXME: This is broken, because the Blocker may be reported to be</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00806" /><CodeLine lineNumber="806"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// liveOnEntry, and we&#39;ll happily wait for that to disappear (read: never)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00807" /><CodeLine lineNumber="807"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// For the moment, this is fine, since we do nothing with blocker info.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00808" /><CodeLine lineNumber="808"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (std::optional&lt;TerminatedPath&gt; Blocker = getBlockingAccess(</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00809" /><CodeLine lineNumber="809"><span class="doxyHighlight">              <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/target">Target</a>, PausedSearches, NewPaused, TerminatedPaths)) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00810" /><CodeLine lineNumber="810"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00811" /><CodeLine lineNumber="811"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Find the node we started at. We can&#39;t search based on N-&gt;Last, since</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00812" /><CodeLine lineNumber="812"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// we may have gone around a loop with a different MemoryLocation.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00813" /><CodeLine lineNumber="813"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">auto</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> Iter = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#ac78c09ae232b2ce188ff590d51e3c268">find&#95;if</a>(def&#95;path(Blocker-&gt;LastNode), &#91;&amp;&#93;(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> DefPath &amp;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/regcomp-c/#a0240ac851181b84ac374872dc5434ee4">N</a>) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00814" /><CodeLine lineNumber="814"><span class="doxyHighlight">          return defPathIndex(N) &lt; PriorPathsSize;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00815" /><CodeLine lineNumber="815"><span class="doxyHighlight">        &#125;);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00816" /><CodeLine lineNumber="816"><span class="doxyHighlight">        <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/silowercontrolflow-cpp/#a4868c5d81c5ccc98c47aeab6244346a0">assert</a>(Iter != def&#95;path&#95;iterator());</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00817" /><CodeLine lineNumber="817"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00818" /><CodeLine lineNumber="818"><span class="doxyHighlight">        DefPath &amp;CurNode = &#42;Iter;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00819" /><CodeLine lineNumber="819"><span class="doxyHighlight">        <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/silowercontrolflow-cpp/#a4868c5d81c5ccc98c47aeab6244346a0">assert</a>(CurNode.Last == Current);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00820" /><CodeLine lineNumber="820"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00821" /><CodeLine lineNumber="821"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Two things:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00822" /><CodeLine lineNumber="822"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// A. We can&#39;t reliably cache all of NewPaused back. Consider a case</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00823" /><CodeLine lineNumber="823"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    where we have two paths in NewPaused; one of which can&#39;t optimize</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00824" /><CodeLine lineNumber="824"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    above this phi, whereas the other can. If we cache the second path</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00825" /><CodeLine lineNumber="825"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    back, we&#39;ll end up with suboptimal cache entries. We can handle</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00826" /><CodeLine lineNumber="826"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    cases like this a bit better when we either try to find all</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00827" /><CodeLine lineNumber="827"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    clobbers that block phi optimization, or when our cache starts</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00828" /><CodeLine lineNumber="828"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    supporting unfinished searches.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00829" /><CodeLine lineNumber="829"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// B. We can&#39;t reliably cache TerminatedPaths back here without doing</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00830" /><CodeLine lineNumber="830"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    extra checks; consider a case like:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00831" /><CodeLine lineNumber="831"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       T</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00832" /><CodeLine lineNumber="832"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//      / \\</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00833" /><CodeLine lineNumber="833"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">        //     D   C</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00834" /><CodeLine lineNumber="834"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//      \\ /</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00835" /><CodeLine lineNumber="835"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       S</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00836" /><CodeLine lineNumber="836"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    Where T is our target, C is a node with a clobber on it, D is a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00837" /><CodeLine lineNumber="837"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    diamond (with a clobber &#42;only&#42; on the left or right node, N), and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00838" /><CodeLine lineNumber="838"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    S is our start. Say we walk to D, through the node opposite N</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00839" /><CodeLine lineNumber="839"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    (read: ignoring the clobber), and see a cache entry in the top</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00840" /><CodeLine lineNumber="840"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    node of D. That cache entry gets put into TerminatedPaths. We then</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00841" /><CodeLine lineNumber="841"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    walk up to C (N is later in our worklist), find the clobber, and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00842" /><CodeLine lineNumber="842"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    quit. If we append TerminatedPaths to OtherClobbers, we&#39;ll cache</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00843" /><CodeLine lineNumber="843"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    the bottom part of D to the cached clobber, ignoring the clobber</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00844" /><CodeLine lineNumber="844"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    in N. Again, this problem goes away if we start tracking all</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00845" /><CodeLine lineNumber="845"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    blockers for a given phi optimization.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00846" /><CodeLine lineNumber="846"><span class="doxyHighlight">        TerminatedPath Result&#123;CurNode.Last, defPathIndex(CurNode)&#125;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00847" /><CodeLine lineNumber="847"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &#123;Result, &#123;&#125;&#125;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00848" /><CodeLine lineNumber="848"><span class="doxyHighlight">      &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00849" /><CodeLine lineNumber="849"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00850" /><CodeLine lineNumber="850"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If there&#39;s nothing left to search, then all paths led to valid clobbers</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00851" /><CodeLine lineNumber="851"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// that we got from our cache; pick the nearest to the start, and allow</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00852" /><CodeLine lineNumber="852"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the rest to be cached back.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00853" /><CodeLine lineNumber="853"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (NewPaused.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectortemplatecommon/#ad9a3c7bc26b130377bbafc170b5f88a2">empty</a>()) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00854" /><CodeLine lineNumber="854"><span class="doxyHighlight">        MoveDominatedPathToEnd(TerminatedPaths);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00855" /><CodeLine lineNumber="855"><span class="doxyHighlight">        TerminatedPath Result = TerminatedPaths.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl/#a0c8ffe664a36e30d49c84d0aded2fe08">pop&#95;back&#95;val</a>();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00856" /><CodeLine lineNumber="856"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &#123;Result, std::move(TerminatedPaths)&#125;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00857" /><CodeLine lineNumber="857"><span class="doxyHighlight">      &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00858" /><CodeLine lineNumber="858"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00859" /><CodeLine lineNumber="859"><span class="doxyHighlight">      <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryaccess">MemoryAccess</a> &#42;DefChainEnd = </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">nullptr</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00860" /><CodeLine lineNumber="860"><span class="doxyHighlight">      <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvector">SmallVector&lt;TerminatedPath, 4&gt;</a> Clobbers;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00861" /><CodeLine lineNumber="861"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (ListIndex Paused : NewPaused) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00862" /><CodeLine lineNumber="862"><span class="doxyHighlight">        UpwardsWalkResult WR = walkToPhiOrClobber(Paths&#91;Paused&#93;);</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00868" /><CodeLine lineNumber="868"><span class="doxyHighlight">      &#125;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00870" /><CodeLine lineNumber="870"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (!TerminatedPaths.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectortemplatecommon/#ad9a3c7bc26b130377bbafc170b5f88a2">empty</a>()) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00871" /><CodeLine lineNumber="871"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If we couldn&#39;t find the dominating phi/liveOnEntry in the above loop,</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00873" /><CodeLine lineNumber="873"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (!DefChainEnd)</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00928" /><CodeLine lineNumber="928"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Finds the nearest clobber for the given query, optimizing phis if</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01297" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1297"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// This class is a batch walker of all MemoryUse&#39;s in the program, and points</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01298" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1298"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// their defining access at the thing that actually clobbers them.  Because it</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01299" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1299"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// is a batch walker that touches everything, it does not operate like the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01300" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1300"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// other walkers.  This walker is basically performing a top-down SSA renaming</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01342" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1342"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Optimize the uses in a given block This is basically the SSA renaming</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01343" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1343"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// algorithm, with one caveat: We are able to use a single stack for all</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01344" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1344"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// MemoryUses.  This is because the set of &#42;possible&#42; reaching MemoryDefs is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01345" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1345"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// the same for every MemoryUse.  The &#42;actual&#42; clobbering MemoryDef is just</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01346" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1346"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// going to be some position in that stack of possible ones.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01347" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1347"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01348" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1348"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// We track the stack positions that each MemoryLocation needs</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01349" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1349"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// to check, and last ended at.  This is because we only want to check the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01350" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1350"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// things that changed since last time.  The same MemoryLocation should</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01351" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1351"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// get clobbered by the same store (getModRefInfo does not use invariantness or</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01352" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1352"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// things like this, and if they start, we can modify MemoryLocOrCall to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01353" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1353"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// include relevant data)</span></CodeLine>
